style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">8%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;over the prior year. The revenue </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">increase</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was driven by organic growth of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">4%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and an increase of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">4%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;from acquisitions, with a negligible impact from foreign exchange. Earnings from continuing operations were </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$232.8 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$1.38</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;diluted earnings per share (&#8220;EPS&#8221;), compared to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$226.2 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$1.31</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;EPS, in the prior year period, representing increases of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">3%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">5%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, respectively. Foreign exchange had a negligible impact. Earnings from continuing operations for the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">nine months</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;ended </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;were </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$626.6 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$3.69</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;EPS, compared to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$651.5 million</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, or </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">$3.75</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;EPS in the prior year period, representing decreases of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">4%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">2%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, respectively.  EPS from continuing operations during this period includes discrete tax benefits of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$0.04</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;EPS compared to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$0.42</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;EPS in the prior year, as well as </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$0.02</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;of other one-time gains recognized in the prior year. Excluding these items, adjusted EPS from continuing operations for the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">nine months</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;ended </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;color:#000000;text-decoration:none;">September&#160;30, 2014</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;was </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$3.65</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, an increase of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">10%</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;over an adjusted EPS of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">$3.31</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;in the prior year.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Commenting on the </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">third</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;quarter results, Dover's President and Chief Executive Officer, Robert A. Livingston, said, &#8220;I was pleased with our strong finish to the third quarter, during which business activity significantly improved in September after softness in July and August. The result for the quarter was revenue and bookings growth at all segments. Most notably, Fluids delivered 17% growth, while Energy and Engineered Systems each grew 8%.  In all, we generated revenue growth of 8%, grew bookings 10%, and saw our backlog increase 14%."</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sBB7D8625517754CFAAD882C6D36B0CBA"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8220;Over the past three quarters, we have made great strides in enhancing our businesses.  We have completed a number of productivity initiatives across the organization and have strengthened several of our businesses with acquisitions, including our recently completed Accelerated transaction. In total, we have invested roughly $800 million on acquisitions year to date.  As a result, we have broadened our product offerings in Artificial Lift, expanded our global footprint in Fluid Transfer, and opened new markets for Printing and Identification.  In addition, we have used our cash flow and balance sheet to grow our annual dividend for the 59</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:7pt">th</sup></font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;consecutive year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">,</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;as well as fund nearly $400 million in share repurchases.&#8221; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">"Looking at the full year, we expect total revenue growth of about 8%.  Organic growth is anticipated to be around 4%.  Completed acquisitions will now provide approximately 4% growth, representing a 1% increase from our prior forecast, principally driven by our recently completed acquisitions. While these deals will have a dilutive impact in 2014, they should be solidly accretive in 2015. In total, we now expect full year adjusted EPS to be in the range of $4.75 to $4.80, a $0.05 reduction to the high end of our prior guidance, largely reflecting the impact of recent acquisitions</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:11pt;">.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221; </font></div><div Dover combines global scale&#160;with operational&#160;agility to lead the markets we serve.&#160;&#160;Recognized&#160;for our entrepreneurial approach for nearly 60&#160;years, our team of 28,000&#160;employees takes an ownership mindset, collaborating with customers to redefine&#160;what&#8217;s&#160;possible.&#160;&#160;Headquartered in&#160;Downers Grove, Illinois, Dover trades on the New York Stock&#160;Exchange&#160;under &#8220;DOV.&#8221; Additional information is available at www.dovercorporation.com.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">Forward-Looking Statements: </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">This press release contains &#8220;forward-looking&#8221; statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995, as amended.
